        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cinnamon Roasted Almonds. A British home-cook's dish — the kind of recipe families adjust across generations. Adjustable for what you need."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A weeknight-friendly recipe: most of the work is the prep, and the cooking takes care of itself."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What you need"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "defaultServings": 4,
          "items": [
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "cinnamon-ground",
              "amount": 2,
              "unit": "tsp",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine",
              "amount": 0.25,
              "unit": "tsp",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "almonds",
              "amount": 2,
              "unit": "cup",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "cooking-spray",
              "amount": null,
              "unit": "ml",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "tone": "info",
          "title": "Also",
          "body": "2 tsp powdered Swerve sweetener."
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Preheat the oven to 350°F."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "In a large bowl, stir together the cinnamon, Swerve, and salt."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Place the almonds in a single layer on a rimmed baking tray, and bake at 350°F for 5 minutes. Remove the tray from the oven, shake it back and forth to move around the almonds, and continue to bake for another 5-7 minutes, or until the almonds are lightly fragrant and toasty."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Immediately mist the nuts with the nonstick cooking spray. Shake the tray a few times, and spray again. Pour the nuts into the bowl with the cinnamon mixture, and toss until completely coated. Let the nuts cool completely to room temperature before transferring to an airtight container."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Notes: Powdered sugar may be substituted for the powdered Swerve sweetener. Powdered sweeteners are best because they “dissolve” better with the cinnamon and stick better to the almonds"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "If you can only find roasted salted almonds, that’s okay. Omit the salt, and bake the almonds for just 4 minutes."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "If something goes wrong",
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "The dish tastes flat",
              "cause": "Underseasoned or no acid.",
              "fix": "Salt a pinch at a time, tasting. A squeeze of lemon or splash of vinegar at the end lifts most savoury dishes."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "It's overcooked by the time it reaches the table",
              "cause": "Carryover cooking — food keeps cooking on the hot pan after the heat goes off.",
              "fix": "Pull off the heat a minute or two before you think it's done. Plate straight away, or transfer to a warmed serving dish."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "It's undercooked in the middle",
              "cause": "Heat too high, browned the outside before the middle warmed through.",
              "fix": "Drop the heat and give it longer. A probe thermometer is the only reliable check for meat."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "The leftovers were dry",
              "cause": "Reheated uncovered, or no liquid in the pan.",
              "fix": "Reheat covered with a splash of stock or water, on a low heat. Microwave on 60% power if using one — gentler than full blast."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Vegetarian swap: replace meat with mushrooms, lentils, or beans — adjust seasoning to compensate."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Spice version: a pinch of chilli flakes or cracked black pepper at the end shifts the dish without losing its character."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about — the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
